    "Tables 3 and 4 show that the performance of classification techniques when using a synergy score of [-10, 10] range to identify the mechanism types of the drugs consistently produced the best accuracy.",
    "Figure 4 shows comparative results of classification techniques using two synergy score ranges in accuracy.",
    "When utilizing the synergy score [-10, 10] range to apply classification approaches, it can be shown that RF provided the best accuracy of the four classifiers evaluated, while LR produced the worst.",
    "It's worth noting, however, that even the worst-performing LR model outperformed a synergy score in the [-5, 5] range in terms of accuracy.",
